## Using Steering Docs

Steering documents in `steering/` are automatically loaded by Kiro to provide context when working on the project. They help Kiro:
- Understand the Frankenstein Lab architecture
- Follow consistent coding patterns
- Know available commands and APIs
- Maintain the spooky theme aesthetic

## Using Hooks

Agent hooks in `hooks/` can be configured to:
- Auto-run tests on file save
- Validate code on commit
- Update documentation automatically
- Run custom workflows

To create your own hooks:
1. Open Command Palette (Ctrl+Shift+P)
2. Search for "Open Kiro Hook UI"
3. Configure your hook triggers and actions

